title: The Latest in High Scool Sports: Volleyball
text: Posted Oct. 19, 2015 at 5:29 PM Updated at 5:31 PM Lake Area Camdenton volleyball takes down Rolla It could have ended quickly when Camdenton hosted Rolla on the volleyball court Thursday night. The Lakers lost the first set 25-23, but came back and took the next two games by scores of 25 to 21. Daphne Dinsdale paced Camdenton with an ace, 13 kills, 11 assists and seven digs. Jordan Wolfe added nine kills and five blocks, Blair Kurtz contributed 10 digs, Tegan Shockley recorded 11 digs and two kills while Hanna Lowther finished the night with 34 digs. The Lakers improved to 13-13-4 on the season and took on Hillcrest (7-14) at 5 p.m., on Monday night in district action at Willard. Osage volleyball sweeps Warsaw Osage had little trouble picking up a win over Warsaw on the road Thursday night. The Indians took the first set by a score of 25-9 and finished the night with a 25-15 win. Maddy Laramore led the Osage attack with seven kills while Kendal Miller finished the night with six of her own respectively. Osage improved to 9-14-4 on the year and the Indians took on California (12-8-3) in district play on Monday night at Blair Oaks. By MICHAEL LOSCH
